author: Inside Edition
description: Police say they have found a decomposed body believed to be 32-year-old Travis Decker, the fugitive accused of murdering his three young daughters, in a remote section of forest where authorities focused their manhunt. Authorities say clothing on the corpse appears to match Decker's. In June, his daughters Paityn, Evelyn, and Olivia were discovered suffocated to death at a campsite in a Washington State national forest.
title: Decomposed Body Believed to Be Travis Decker Found: Police

author: Inside Edition
description: Late night comics are coming to the defense of Jimmy Kimmel the way they know best, with humor. The Daily Show set was decked out in gold, mimicking President Donald Trump's love of gilded decor. Steven Colbert opened with a spoof from Disney's "Beauty and the Beast." Colbert also resurrected his classic “Colbert Report” persona. Jimmy Fallon used punchlines about Trump were dubbed over with compliments. Seth Myers paid a sarcastic tribute to the president.
title: Late Night Comics Use Humor In Defense Of Jimmy Kimmel

author: Inside Edition
description: Jimmy Kimmel was in talks Friday to get his show back. He was spotted heading into a meeting with an entertainment lawyer and is in negotiations with Disney to end his suspension. According to reports, Disney executives asked Kimmel to apologize for his comments about Charlie Kirk's alleged killer, but Kimmel refused and was planning another fiery monologue, and that's when the plug was pulled on his show. Late night veteran Jay Leno says he's hopeful Kimmel will be back on the air.
title: Jimmy Kimmel Trying To Get His Show Back On Air

author: Inside Edition
description: Deputies responded to a home invasion after a report that four suspects attempted to break in. There were no suspects in sight. Then they announced their arrival. The homeowner unlocked his door and a deputy fired his gun, shooting him. The injured man was led away for medical help. The sheriff department in Orange County, Florida, said the deputy "accidentally discharged his firearm." He's been "temporarily reassigned to an administrative capacity" as the investigation continues.
title: Deputy 'Accidentally' Shot Homeowner Following Home Invasion Report

author: Inside Edition
description: Charlene Kirby was cleaning her ranch for her grandson's wedding when she hoped in her side-by-side to dump some debris. The vehicle jackknifed, and she fell, breaking her leg. It was 7 p.m. and the 75-year-old retired nurse was a quarter of a mile from her house in McCoy, Colorado. What followed was an extraordinary effort to save herself. Kirby crawled on her stomach for 14 hours to safety. She spoke with Inside Edition's Jim Moret.
title: 75-Year-Old Woman With Broken Leg Crawls 14 Hours Towards Home

author: Inside Edition
description: First Lady Melania Trump and Princess Kate met kids in the scouts movement Thursday and joined in with arts and crafts projects.
title: Princess Kate And Melania Trump Meet Kids #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: This donkey has been going through it lately. Rescuers in California say the wild burro was found with an arrow sticking out from its side. She was taken in by rescue organization DonkeyLand and given an apt name, Cupid. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Wild Burro Recovering After Being Shot by Arrow in California

author: Inside Edition
description: Ice and Kali are working dogs. You might not know it from their calm demeanors, but that's the point: they're trained to help young victims and witnesses make their way through the justice system in Maine. Ice's human, Paul Rucha, told Inside Edition Digital that "Ice is the chillest dog you ever want to meet," and that Ice's calming presence can help people get through very difficult situations. "Just having a dog there that you can pet lowers that anxiety level," he added.
title: These Chill Working Dogs Help Young Witnesses and Victims

author: Inside Edition
description: The passing of Hollywood icon Robert Redford is reigniting interest in a tantalizing cold case from 1983.
title: Who Killed Robert Redford's Son-In-Law #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A car sped up to a hospital with a special delivery on board, a mom in labor. Dad got out, thinking he was going to help her inside, but he realized the baby's head had already appeared. Within seconds, a hospital volunteer made her way to the car and the president of the hospital happened to walk by when it was all unfolding. Suddenly, an army of hospital staff poured out, but the hero dad had already delivered a baby girl, named Kamilah.
title: Dad Delivers Baby in Hospital Parking Lot

author: Inside Edition
description: Kavan Markwood fell 21 feet from the nosebleed seats onto the field – and against all odds, he survived. He spoke exclusively to Inside Edition's Steve Fabian.
title: What Fan Who Plummeted Over Stadium Railing Told Steven Fabian #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Robert Irwin, son of crocodile hunter Steve Irwin, and brother of Bindi Irwin, stole the show at this season's premiere of "Dancing With The Stars."
title: Robert Irwin Steals The Show At 'Dancing With The Stars' shorts
